		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Cassindra's Changes - WOOT<a name="12047"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 11 03 2:57 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span> The debate on wether this is an upgrade or a nerf is rooted in how you're using the song. If you're twisting it in a battle, etc, it is nice that it will hit three times, so it looks like an upgrade. But consider the times when you're not in a fight and the group needs mana, you can no longer fold this song, rendering you helpless to sit there and wait. 
<br />

<br />
 For those who've never folded--This song used to be a direct mana song, alllowing a bard who knows what their doing to twist it on top of itself (recast it everytime it ticks), making the song tick over twice as fast. Now all folding does it put the buff back on, something that can be done by just leaving it playing.
<br />

<br />
 By eliminating the ability to assault casters with an onslaught of amplified clarity, I consider this more of a nerf, but I can appreciate the slight upgrade of it.
<br />

<br />
All-in-all... the new mana song is slower, but it lasts longer. Judge it how you will.
<br />

<br />
-my 2 cents</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
